⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Chozo
node MET · MET · ⟦The Chozo:MET:136770⟧

WHO   — The Chozo — the vanished progenitors
WHAT  — The vanished progenitors of the Metroid universe — who infused the child Samus with their strength, crafted her Power Suit, and left behind the ruins, the guardian statues, and the gifts she gathers in the dark.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because they foresaw the Metroid menace and the ruin it would bring; because a child of the destroyed colony needed strength to survive a hostile galaxy; and because their work was always to spread peace and prepare a hand to carry it after they were gone.
HOW   — By prophecy and patient making — by infusing Samus with Chozo strength, by forging the cybernetic Power Suit and arm cannon, and by hiding their gifts inside guardian statues across Zebes for the hunter to find.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We are gone from the galaxy, but our hand still shapes it — we raised the orphan, forged her armor, and hid our strength in stone for her to find.

spoken token : reith-lis-phom   ·   hex : 136770
